args:
The prince and his companions rescue
Elisanne, a Paladyn from the Ilian Church.
She offers to repay this kindness by
joining them as their bodyguard.
Tsk! This is more than I bargained for.\nBut I'll be back!
Keep sticking your head into my affairs\nand watch how fast you lose it.
Having thwarted the assassin's gambit,\nour companions travel on until they find\na place to rest beneath the trees.
I'm so glad we arrived in time.\nWhat is your name, Paladyn?
I am Elisanne. And you are the maiden\nZethia, are you not?
You are the Ilian Auspex and a member of\nthe royal family, my lady.
So yes, of course I know of you.\nWhat Paladyn wouldn't?
We are sworn to protect you and all\nmembers of the cloth.
Only a handful of the Church's knights\nare strong enough to become Paladyns.
Wait a sec. If you kick so much butt,\nthen why'd that chump give you so\nmuch trouble earlier?
Forgive me, but I'd rather not discuss\nthe matter.
You wouldn't even tell the Auspex?
Very well. I respect your decision.\nBut at least let me attend to your wounds.
Heh. I suppose it shouldn't surprise me\nthat the Auspex knows a thing or two\nabout restorative magic.
Well, I have to be good at something.
Zethia has saved my hide more times than\nI can count.
Hee hee. Because you're constantly\ngetting yourself into trouble!
Maybe I'm only good at healing because\nmy brother gives me so much practice.
Your brother...? Hold a moment!\nAre you Prince {player_name}?!\nThe king's seventh child?
I thought you were her manservant!\nOh, but this is simply mortifying.\nI am deeply sorry, Your Highness.
Yeah, he gets that a lot.\nMust be the hair.
I don't know what I was thinking!
It is a great honor to be in the company\nof yourself and your younger sister,\nYour Highness.
Ha! Really, it's not that big a deal. I'm not\nhalf as famous as my elder siblings.
But now that you're here, do you know\nwhere we can find the Mistholt?
We've been trying to reach it for some\ntime now without much success.
The Mistholt? Mmm, I've heard of it...
Yes, there was a mercenary in Rovetelle\nwho claimed to have encountered a\ndragon in a mist-cloaked wood.
That must be it! Thank you, Lady Elisanne.\nWe'll pay Rovetelle a visit right away.
With your permission, might I accompany\nyou as your bodyguard?
It's the least I can do to repay you,\nmy lady.
If ever I prove to be a burden, you may\nfeel free to dismiss me at once.
Dismiss you? We'd be lucky to have a\nknight like you by our side! You're more\nthan welcome to come with us.
Whenever I heal someone, I get a glimpse\ninto their character.
I can tell you have a pure heart,\nLady Elisanne. As the goddess Ilia\nis my witness, I know it to be true.
Hey, no objections here.\nI'm good with whatever!
Thank you all. I promise to serve you\nloyally and well, Your Highness.
Great! Er, but promise me one thing...
Can you ease up on the formalities?\nWe'd rather you feel relaxed with us.
We've got a long journey ahead of us,\nand it'll be a lot less stuffy for you to just\nuse my name instead of ＂Your Highness.＂
＂My lady＂ and ＂Auspex＂ grow tiresome\nafter a while.
I'd sooner tear my own tongue out and\nthrow it into the flames!
Ugh, GROSS! Please do NOT do that.\n...Oh, and I'm Notte, by the way.
...Very well. I'll do my best to be less\nformal with you all.
After all, how difficult can it be?\nRight, Ze... Z-Zeth...?\n*sigh* This is not working.
Well, I suppose it'll take some getting\nused to, but I'll get there eventually.\nNow shall we be off?
